Class AggregationFunction<P,A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.math.functions.AggregationFunction<P,A>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the aggregated values.
    A - the return type of the function, i.e., the type of the aggregate.

    public abstract class AggregationFunction<P,A>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    An aggregation-function is a binary function that computes an aggregate. The function is called with the last aggregate and the next value that should be added to the aggregate. Calling the function with an aggregate set to null initializes the aggregation-function, i.e., the function acts as it is called the very first time.

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        public abstract A invoke(A aggregate,
                         P value)
        Returns the result of the aggregation-function as an object of the aggregate type. The function is invoked with the last aggregation value (the last status of the aggregation) and the next value that should be considered by the aggregation-function.
        Parameters:
        aggregate - the last aggregate returned by the function. When it is set to null the aggregation-function is initialized, i.e., it acts as it is called the very first time.
        value - the next value that should be considered by the aggregation-function.
        Returns:
        the new aggregate.
